---
title: "create-component — Generic Orchestrator Flow"
---
%%{init: {'theme': 'neutral'}}%%
sequenceDiagram
    actor U as User
    participant S as Skill
    participant R as Registry
    participant F as Figma
    participant FS as FileSystem
    participant A as Adapter

    U->>S: /create-component <name> [figma-url]

    note over S: Step 0 — Pre-flight
    S->>S: TodoWrite — init all tasks pending
    S->>FS: read template + registry + analysis
    note over S: extract naming_conventions<br/>+ styling_system + typography_file

    critical Figma token check
        S->>F: whoami
        F-->>S: authenticated
    option EC5 — token invalid
        S-->>U: stop — fix FIGMA_ACCESS_TOKEN
    end

    S->>FS: check if <name>/ directory exists (even if empty)

    opt EC2 — directory exists, name not in registry
        S-->>U: dir exists but not in registry<br/>overwrite / register as-is / cancel?
        U-->>S: choice
    end

    S->>F: get_code_connect_suggestions(nodeId, fileKey)
    F-->>S: mainComponentNodeId

    alt nodeId is a variant (mainComponentNodeId ≠ nodeId)
        S-->>U: STOP — this is a variant node, not a component set<br/>Please provide the parent ◆◆ component set URL
        U-->>S: parent component set URL
        S->>S: parse new fileKey + nodeId from parent URL
    end

    note over S: Phase 0.5 — Variant Analysis and Plan

    S->>F: get_design_context(nodeId, disableCodeConnect)
    F-->>S: all N variants with properties<br/>(e.g. type=prim|sec, state=default|hover|disabled)

    note over S: for each variant — lightweight analysis<br/>(layout differences, unique tokens, typography)

    S-->>U: show implementation plan
    note over U: "Component Set: <name> (N variants)<br/>☑ prim / default — ...<br/>☑ prim / hover — ...<br/>☑ sec / default — ...<br/>Uncheck variants you don't need. Confirm to proceed."

    U-->>S: selected variants confirmed

    note over S: Phase 1 — Context (3 parallel)

    par Agent 1 — Figma design
        S->>F: get_design_context(nodeId, fileKey)
        F-->>S: layout + colors + typography
        S->>F: get_design_context(nodeId, disableCodeConnect)
        F-->>S: full structure + variants + icon nodes list
    and Agent 2 — Reuse check
        S->>R: load registry (match by figma_node_id OR name)
        R-->>S: known components
        note over R: EXACT / PARTIAL / NO match
        opt EXACT match
            S->>FS: grep component name in source
            FS-->>S: N usages
        end
    and Agent 3 — Token + typography sync
        S->>FS: read token file + typography file
        S->>F: get_variable_defs(nodeId, fileKey)
        F-->>S: Figma design variables
        note over S: color/spacing: compare by value<br/>matched / missing
        note over S: typography: match text styles<br/>by font-size + weight + line-height<br/>against existing @mixin definitions
    end

    alt EXACT MATCH + N usages > 0
        S-->>U: already exists — reusing
    else EXACT MATCH + 0 usages
        S-->>U: exists but unused — add variant or update?
        U-->>S: choice
    else PARTIAL MATCH
        S-->>U: extend or refactor?
        U-->>S: choice
    else EC2 — on disk, not in registry
        S-->>U: overwrite / register / cancel?
        U-->>S: choice
    end

    opt EC3b — token name mismatch
        S-->>U: Figma name vs local name — map or skip?
        U-->>S: confirmed
    end

    opt EC11 — no Figma tokens
        S-->>U: proceed with empty / cancel?
        U-->>S: choice
    end

    opt typography gap — no matching mixin
        S-->>U: no mixin for {size}/{weight}/{lh}<br/>create new or use closest?
        U-->>S: mixin name confirmed
    end

    opt Phase 1.5 — Composite detected
        note over S: Decompose bottom-up
        S->>S: build dependency tree (deepest first)
        note over S: classify each child by layer
        note over S: build children before parent
    end

    note over S: Phase 2 — Implement

    opt EC6 — special chars in name
        S-->>U: converted name preview
        U-->>S: confirm / edit
    end

    par Stream A — Download assets
        loop each icon node
            S->>F: fetch SVG (nodeId)
            F-->>FS: img/<kebab-name>.svg
        end
    and Stream B — Generate code
        S->>FS: add missing tokens to token file
        S->>A: generate(template, tokens, mixins,<br/>variants, layer, styling_system)
        note over A: adapter writes CSS + JS<br/>+ preview file
        A-->>FS: component files written
        S->>FS: register @import in main CSS
        S->>S: run component-done checklist
    end

    opt EC4 — no icons detected
        note over S: log note, continue
    end

    opt EC12 — child not in registry
        note over S: create as local — non-blocking
    end

    opt Phase 3 — Visual verify
        S->>A: visual_verify(component, figma_ref)
        note over A: adapter-specific<br/>(SSIM / screenshot / etc.)
        A-->>S: pass / fail + report
    end

    note over S: Phase 4 — Registry
    S->>R: upsert(name, type, layer,<br/>path, figma_node_id, status)
    R-->>S: written

    note over S: Phase 5 — Code Connect
    S->>FS: scan for primitive (*.figma.ts / *.figma.js)

    alt EC13 — no primitive found
        S-->>U: no CC pattern yet — pick a simple primitive<br/>(no children) to establish it
        U-->>S: Figma URL for primitive
        note over S: run inline primitive creation<br/>(Phases 1–4 + CC setup)
        note over S: then resume here
    end

    S->>FS: read primitive → extract CC pattern
    note over S: discovers format + template + publish cmd

    S->>F: get_code_connect_map(nodeId, fileKey)
    F-->>S: existing mappings (if any)

    opt existing CC mapping
        S-->>U: show old → new — replace?
        U-->>S: confirmed
    end

    S->>FS: write <name>.figma.{ext}
    S->>A: cc_publish(--dry-run)
    A-->>S: validation ok
    S->>A: cc_publish
    A-->>S: published

    S-->>U: done — files + registry + Code Connect

    note over S,A: Tool Failure Pattern
    note over S: critical tool fails → stop + structured report
    note over S: non-critical tool fails → log, continue
